The paper deals with deep image classification models and their application to semantic segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for semantic segmentation, which involves careful architectural considerations and modelling power, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of GPUs and memory limitations, which suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and computer systems and networking (cs.CL).
